.TH "spu_yield" 9 "spu_yield" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spu_yield \- yield a physical spu if others are waiting
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" spu_yield
.BI "(struct spu_context *ctx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
spu context to yield
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check if there is a higher priority context waiting and if yes
unbind \fIctx\fP from the physical spu and schedule the highest
priority context to run on the freed physical spu instead.
